    <equation id="eip-54"><m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mn>6</m:mn><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">+</m:mo><m:msub><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mtext>45</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>0</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/><m:mo>.</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{+6I rSub { size 8{1} } +2I rSub { size 8{3} }  - "45"=0} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math></equation><para id="import-auto-id1402503">These three equations are sufficient to solve for the three unknown currents. First, solve the second equation for <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>I</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{I rSub { size 8{2} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>:</para>
